# PixelForge Environment Variables

# ====================
# Solana Configuration
# ====================

# Solana network (devnet or mainnet-beta)
# Used for documentation purposes
NEXT_PUBLIC_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet

# Solana RPC endpoint
# Default: https://api.devnet.solana.com
# For mainnet: https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com
# Or use a custom RPC like Helius, QuickNode, etc.
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_ENDPOINT=https://api.devnet.solana.com

# Collection mint address (optional)
# If set, newly minted NFTs will be added to this collection
# Generate a collection first, then paste the mint address here
NEXT_PUBLIC_COLLECTION_MINT=DVgMx8qW7P9238p991viJdmsgMatnoLNJtobVeaQrHkP

# ====================
# Collection Authority
# ====================

# Collection update authority private key (REQUIRED)
# Format: JSON array of 64 numbers [1,2,3,...,64]
# This keypair is used to:
#  - Pay for NFT minting transactions
#  - Sign collection updates (if using a collection)
#
# Generate with: solana-keygen new --outfile keypair.json --no-bip39-passphrase
# Then copy the array from keypair.json
#
# ⚠️  KEEP THIS SECRET! Never commit to git or share publicly
COLLECTION_UPDATE_AUTHORITY=

# ====================
# ArDrive Turbo (Arweave Storage)
# ====================

# Arweave JWK (JSON Web Key) for ArDrive Turbo uploads (REQUIRED)
# Used to upload images and metadata to Arweave
#
# Option 1: Base64-encoded JWK (RECOMMENDED for production)
# Generate with: cat key.json | base64
TURBO_JWK_BASE64=

# Option 2: Raw JSON JWK (alternative)
# Paste the entire JWK JSON on one line
TURBO_JWK_JSON=

# Option 3: Local development only
# Place key.json in the project root (fallback if env vars not set)
# ⚠️  DO NOT use key.json in production!

# ====================
# Setup Instructions
# ====================

# 1. Generate Solana keypair:
#    solana-keygen new --outfile keypair.json --no-bip39-passphrase
#    cat keypair.json
#    Copy the array into COLLECTION_UPDATE_AUTHORITY
#
# 2. Get Arweave wallet for Turbo:
#    - Create wallet at https://arweave.app/
#    - Download JWK file
#    - Base64 encode: cat arweave-key.json | base64
#    - Paste into TURBO_JWK_BASE64
#
# 3. Fund your Turbo account:
#    - Visit https://app.ardrive.io/#/turbo
#    - Connect your Arweave wallet
#    - Add credits (accepts SOL, AR, and other tokens)
#
# 4. (Optional) Create NFT collection:
#    - Use Metaplex CLI or Sugar to create a collection
#    - Paste collection mint address into NEXT_PUBLIC_COLLECTION_MINT
#
# 5. For devnet testing:
#    - Get devnet SOL: solana airdrop 2 <your-public-key> --url devnet
#    - Fund Turbo with devnet tokens
